        </span>.
        <br/><br/>
        <strong><font color="blue">Electron Capture (EC)</font> </strong>:  A K orbital electron can be captured by a proton-rich nucleus. This leaves a hole in the K-shell (see other slide on filling holes). A proton decay will occur, and a neutrino (only) will be emitted.

